# Xevu Project Instructions

## Overview
MCP server analyzing React codebases through behavioral user archetypes for UX feedback.

## Rules
- ES modules only — `import/export`, never `require()`
- Use `.js` extension in relative imports (Node16 module resolution)
- All types in `src/shared/types.ts` — single source of truth
- All logging to stderr — stdout is MCP JSON-RPC transport
- Pipeline stages return `Result<T, E>` — never throw exceptions
- Read-only — never modify user code

## Architecture
6-stage pipeline: Scan → Parse → Domain → Flow → Archetypes → Report
Each stage in `src/pipeline/<stage>/` returns `Result<T, E>`.

## Commands
- `npm run lint` — type check
- `npm test` — run all tests
- `npm run build` — compile TypeScript
- `npm run format` — format with Prettier

## See AGENTS.md for complete instructions.
